Several key points of the updated function:
1. When the node with two children is deleted, we find the inorder successor (the smallest node in the right subtree, as retrieved by `minValueNode`). We copy its value to the node being deleted.
2. We then delete the inorder successor recursively with `root->right = Delete(root->right, temp->data);`.
3. We must update the `top` pointer of the `AVL` tree if the node being deleted is the root of the entire tree.
4. Make sure to set the parent pointer of any child when a node is deleted, so when you delete a node `root`, and it has a single child `temp`, you set `temp->parent` to the parent of the root.
5. When we delete `root` and assign it to `temp`, we are changing the pointer; thus, we should delete the old `root`.

